<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99387623227391></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99387623227391><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99387623227391>RE: what weapon?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99387623227391#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Jun 30th 12:43 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As for what you wrote about Ideal for wisdom\piercing weapons, you are a bit off there. <br><br>For primary weapon I would say Spine Chill Spear, good dmg\delay ratio and 6 wisdom, 3 sta, and 5 CR. <br><br>For Secondary hand I would say Testament of Vanear, 10 wis, 10 mana. Might not get the AC from the the shield but it's mana you were after, and the testament has more.<br><br>For ranged weapon Howling Harpoon has it there. If you can't afford a Howling Harpoon the Ebon War Spear isnt' that bad either, and you can get it yourself at around 30. goes for 200pp i think, 3 wis.<br><br>For those 3 items it would raise your wisdom by roughly 25 and your mana by around 30. For any shamans planning on taking the 2hb route, let me advise you against it. When you get to high lvls, you aren't going to be soloing that much. True you can do it, I do it all the time, but when you do solo, you don't melee more than you have to. I'm 45, i have about 1000 hp, the mobs double for around 90 or so. statistics tell you you won't last that long. Just root and dot. I dont' even bother with pet since he dies to fast and doesn't do enough dmg for the mana it costs to summon him. just root, malise, and dot.. sit back and watch the fireworks. your weapons will give you mana and the dmg on them is quite nice also for when you do melee. also have the effect of shock of ice, a 40 dd. Anyways, that is my advice.<br><br>Devta Wolfkin, Shaman of the 45th season, Druzzil Ror<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
